dataElements.name: GPPI | Deliveries (no disaggregation by type)
dataElements.description:
Refers to the total number of women who delivered a live baby or stillbirth/fetal death at a given period.

Note:
Complete delivery refers to the delivery of the newborn/fetus (whether dead or alive) up to the complete expulsion of the placenta from the mother’s womb.
• Multiple births by a woman is counted as 1 delivery
• Deliveries by caesarian section and assisted vaginal delivery are included in this count.
• Abortion/miscarriage is not included in the counts of deliveries

Deliveries should be reported by place of occurrence. Reconcile TCL and LCR (check both TCL and LCR to ensure all are captured and avoid duplication of reporting).

dataElements.description:
Refers to the total number of women who delivered a live baby or stillbirth/fetal death at a given period.

Note:
Complete delivery refers to the delivery of the newborn/fetus (whether dead or alive) up to the complete expulsion of the placenta from the mother’s womb.
• Multiple births by a woman is counted as 1 delivery
• Deliveries by caesarian section and assisted vaginal delivery are included in this count.
• Abortion/miscarriage is not included in the counts of deliveries

Deliveries should be reported by place of occurrence. Reconcile TCL and LCR (check both TCL and LCR to ensure all are captured and avoid duplication of reporting).
